  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Bloody Knuckles Street Boxing is a physics based boxing game made by a long time boxing enthusiast who also enjoys gritty fighting games. It's time to put your boxing IQ to the test.... IN THE STREETS! </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Here are some things that you will experience:</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Total control movement system</strong> with user controlled lateral movement and pivots.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Over 30 punch animations</strong> with user controlled target tracking.</p></li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Pressure sensitive controller mechanics</strong> that transform your boxer into a digital puppet.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Adjust defensively</strong> by switching your guard in real time. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Highly effective counter punching</strong> from slick head movement and parries.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Organic clinch system</strong> with realistic physics.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>AI sparring with AI action presets</strong> to help you master your strategy.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Training games</strong> including shadow boxing and FOCUS MITTS!</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>SATISFYING RAGDOLL KNOCKOUTS!</strong></p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>***WARNING</strong>***</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Bloody Knuckles Street Boxing is NOT your average boxing game. You are in control of EVERYTHING your fighter does from punch placement to obeying the rules. Your hand will NOT be held any way. This game is backed by a community of true boxing connoisseurs looking for a place to exercise their knowledge of the sweet science. The goal is to create an OBVIOUS skill gap between users. If easy wins are what you're looking for, I recommend trying other boxing games. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
  "about_the_game": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Bloody Knuckles Street Boxing is a physics based boxing game made by a long time boxing enthusiast who also enjoys gritty fighting games. It's time to put your boxing IQ to the test.... IN THE STREETS! </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Here are some things that you will experience:</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" > </p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Total control movement system</strong> with user controlled lateral movement and pivots.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Over 30 punch animations</strong> with user controlled target tracking.</p></li></ul><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Pressure sensitive controller mechanics</strong> that transform your boxer into a digital puppet.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Adjust defensively</strong> by switching your guard in real time. </p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Highly effective counter punching</strong> from slick head movement and parries.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Organic clinch system</strong> with realistic physics.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>AI sparring with AI action presets</strong> to help you master your strategy.</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Training games</strong> including shadow boxing and FOCUS MITTS!</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>SATISFYING RAGDOLL KNOCKOUTS!</strong></p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>***WARNING</strong>***</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Bloody Knuckles Street Boxing is NOT your average boxing game. You are in control of EVERYTHING your fighter does from punch placement to obeying the rules. Your hand will NOT be held any way. This game is backed by a community of true boxing connoisseurs looking for a place to exercise their knowledge of the sweet science. The goal is to create an OBVIOUS skill gap between users. If easy wins are what you're looking for, I recommend trying other boxing games. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
